%\subsection{Closed Huygens\rq~Box}\label{Closed_Huygen_s_Box}

Six-sided rectangular box of virtual surface locus S that enclosed the structure of interest in the scattering field-zone of FDTD lattice is known as Huygens\rq~Box. The electric and magnetic current on the closed Huygens\rq~surface are computed by using the FDTD method, and the far-field pattern is subsequently obtained from the equivalent current sources (see Fig.~\ref{Fig:huygen_box}) \cite{Mittra_CFDTD_04}. Because the electric and magnetic fields have a half-cell of deviation in Yee\rq s scheme, the field on the Huygens\rq~surface are averaged from those around the surface, shown in Fig.~\ref{Fig:equivalent_field_on_the_surface_of_Huygen_box}.

